annotation.TEXT: Well, that was a failed block factory attempt.
Fuzzies that aren't line-guided can be shell-killed, but line-guided ones are invincible.
Nothing of interest. Alright.
27? I should've been able to do way better than that. (Interestingly, this makes my average exactly 30 now.)
Darn it, another mushroom.
Hey, there Mr. Bob-- Whoops! Wasn't expecting that. Well, there's another Mr. "Bob--" here that I can greet...
Gotta check every pipe... And properly aim for the center of the pipe while doing so.

Huh, so the original block contained a vine, which is why I got coins, as block cloning a vine block to the right gives you a "Star 2", which is a star if you're currently invincible, and a coin if you aren't. (Cloning the vine block to the left would've given me a 1-up.)
Goal tape average so far: 243 / 8 = 30.375 stars each.
D'oh, so much for that mushroom that I totally missed there.
6-life combo!
Wow, what's with all the French curves in the lines here? Definitely makes it more challenging to read the saw and Fuzzy movements.
BLOCK FACTORYYY!!!

Well, it looks like there aren't any branching paths left in this hack, since it's only a 2-world demo (so no more voting). And actually, I'll probably finish up this hack next time! To be continued... Yo!
And, I'm back at midpoint. Alright, let's head back to the right.
Whoa, that was kinda cool. Okay, enough with the fancy stunts already.
That Chuck knows how to dig it.

Seriously, this is a lot of curves! I really hope I have enough time to get to the end of this line-guide ride!

Okay, I hit the right one, but can I hit the middle one that way, or should I just jump to one of the mushroom platforms on the side in order to raise the height of one of the center mushroom platforms? ...Yeah, I should probably do that.

But, I can totally do a shell jump to get up there instead!
Well, it's got platforms... And a disco shell... And I hear a saw nearby...

BGM: We ♥ Katamari - Katamari on the Swing

Excellent! And I started that stomping combo before I kicked the shell into the bubble for the 9-life combo, so it's kinda like... "Yo, dude. I heard you like combos, so I put a combo in your combo so that you can combo while you combo."
...Huh. There's hardly any difference in the animation when I press down while holding something. The shell moves down a pixel, and one pixel in BJ's mouth changes color. That's about it I think.
Oh, that block looks like it's set up perfectly for me to "block factory" it!
Oh, ho, ho! This ! coin is only visible if you're on the upper path, so you have to check out both paths in order to get every ! coin.

And yet, I'm still getting slowdown, but that's probably a good thing here, because it looks like I can get a nice stomping combo here, and the slowdown will help with that!
Oh, there's where the chocolate cake picture went! So, the cake wasn't a lie after all! It was just irregularly scheduled!
Well, I only got 30 stars, but the shell I carried through the goal has become an extra Fire Flower for BJ2! Nice!

But, I'm pretty sure he didn't dig me stomping on him. Okay, so there's midpoint, and I have 2 ! coins so far. But, will there be 3 in the second half?
Ah, this looks more icy, although I'm no longer in a cave now.
9-life combo!

"COME ON, EVERYBODY!"
Hello, and welcome back to Bowser Jr.'s Adventure! Let's see what the votes have to say this time...

...Huh? Where's the chocolate cake picture? ...Aw, did I forget to insert it into the video? Nuts! Well, sorry folks, but I'm not remaking and reuploading this video now. I guess that this time... The cake is a lie.
